The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Maruti price hike spares 800

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 New Delhi, Jan. 5: Maruti Udyog Limited (MUL) today formally announced the price hike for its various models. 

 Speaking to The Telegraph, a company spokesperson said, ?The price increase has been in the range of 0.3 to 1.3 per cent for different models. However, the price of the Maruti 800 is still being worked out and will be finalised soon. 

 The price hike has been in the range of Rs 2000-3000, the spokesperson said. The multi-utility vehicle (MUV), Gypsy, costs Rs 3000 more. The Maruti Omni is also dearer by Rs 3000. 

 For all other variants, there has been a price rise of Rs 2000, the spokesperson said. These include the Alto, Wagon R and Zen, which fall in the A2 segment. The Baleno and Esteem fall in the upper segment. Another high-end vehicle in the SUV segment is Vitara. 

 The spokesperson said, ?The price rise is because of an increase in input costs for production.? The hike was on expected lines as the prices of aluminum and steel has been escalating in the recent past. 

 The Maruti 800, which is the entry-level car in the company?s portfolio, is at present coming with a price tag of Rs 2.05 lakh for the standard version and 2.28 lakh for the air-conditioned one (ex-show room price, Delhi). Baleno, in the top-end, is priced at Rs 5.62 lakh for the base version and at Rs 6.32 lakh for the VXI ? a higher version.

 In a communication to all dealers, Maruti had recently informed them of a likely increase in prices in January. 




